<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,454,403,429]" box="[189,454,403,429]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,403,429]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,403,429]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[188,1400,450,621]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,647,450,477]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illustratoides" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Floccocheila">
<emphasis box="[189,302,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[320,473,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Floccocheila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[492,647,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">illustratoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[656,748,451,477]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[888,1133,450,476]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indistincta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[888,1133,450,476]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Cheilosia indistincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1141,1233,451,477]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1294,1400,450,477]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vellea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1294,1400,450,477]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">C. vellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,284,487,513]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and from these species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[578,770,486,513]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illustratoides">
<emphasis box="[578,770,486,513]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">C. illustratoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by mostly long yellow pilosity of femora (vs predominantly black in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[461,618,522,549]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indistincta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[461,618,522,549]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">C. indistincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[623,712,523,549]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[764,868,522,549]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vellea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[764,868,522,549]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">C. vellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[873,965,523,549]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[984,1224,522,548]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indistincta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[984,1224,522,548]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Cheilosia indistincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1230,1319,523,549]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[252,355,558,585]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vellea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[252,355,558,585]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">C. vellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[360,449,559,585]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having only yellow pilosity on lateral margin of tergite I (vs with black pilosity in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[219,323,595,621]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vellea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[219,323,595,621]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">C. vellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[331,425,595,621]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), all species differ by structure of male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,324,661,687]" box="[189,324,661,687]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,661,687]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,661,687]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[189,1399,708,771]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
The specific epithet ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[432,587,708,734]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illustratoides">
<emphasis box="[432,587,708,734]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">illustratoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ is from the Latin ‘ 
<emphasis box="[809,926,708,734]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">illustrates</emphasis>
’, meaning ‘clear, enlightened’, referring to the resemblance of the new species with the Palearctic 
<taxonomicName authority="(Harris, 1780)" baseAuthorityName="Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1780" box="[865,1270,744,770]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illustrata">
<emphasis box="[865,1093,744,770]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Cheilosia illustrata</emphasis>
(Harris, 1780)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
